cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about a benchmark collection for research on learning distributed word representations, which is a topic related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the evaluation of different machine learning algorithms on the benchmark, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses potential research topics related to word embeddings, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
